T1  - Matching and Inequality in the World Economy
AU  - Costinot, Arnaud
AU  - Vogel, Jonathan
Y1  - 2010/08/01
PY  - 2010
DA  - 2010/08/01
N1  - doi: 10.1086/655858
DO  - 10.1086/655858
T2  - Journal of Political Economy
JF  - Journal of Political Economy
SP  - 747
EP  - 786
VL  - 118
IS  - 4
PB  - The University of Chicago Press
N2  - This paper develops tools and techniques to analyze the determinants of factor allocation and factor prices in economies with a large number of goods and factors. The main results of our paper characterize sufficient conditions for robust monotone comparative statics predictions in a Roy-like assignment model. These general results are then used to generate new insights about the consequences of globalization.
AB  - This paper develops tools and techniques to analyze the determinants of factor allocation and factor prices in economies with a large number of goods and factors. The main results of our paper characterize sufficient conditions for robust monotone comparative statics predictions in a Roy-like assignment model. These general results are then used to generate new insights about the consequences of globalization.
SN  - 0022-3808
M3  - doi: 10.1086/655858
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1086/655858
Y2  - 2024/03/20
